              Distance
              Double-click on the map to add points and measure distance between them. To move a point, left-click it and drag to another place holding the left mouse button. To delete a point, double-click it.

              Area
              Double-click on the map to draw an area. To move a point, left-click it and drag to another place holding the left mouse button. To delete a point, double-click it.

              Track hittest
              Choose the track you need in the dropdown menu. Double-click on the track to request information about any of its points. Switch to the multipoint mode to set several markers at once.

                              Track player
                              To add tracks to Track player, use one of the following methods:

                              – Build tracks on the "Tracks" tab.
                              – Request messages on the "Messages" tab. The track is mapped automatically.
                              – Generate a report with the activated "Trip routes" or "All messages on map" option in the report template.
                              – Activate the "Quick track" option on the "Monitoring" tab.
                              Help

                              Create a point:  double-click on the map.

                              Insert a point:  double-click on a segment between two points.

                              Delete a point:  double-click on a point.

                              Move a point:  drag a point to another place holding the left mouse button.

                              Double-click on a unit in the work list to open it in an individual tracking window.
